  - add EUC-TW (euctw) script encoding, ported from the legacy Char-EUCTW /
    Eeuctw engine.  This is the first mb encoding with an \x8E (SS2) four-octet
    structure: CNS 11643 plane 1 is [\xA1-\xFE][\xA1-\xFE] (2 octets) and the
    SS2 planes 2..16 are \x8E[\xA1-\xB0][\xA1-\xFE][\x00-\xFF] (4 octets).
    Touched in lib/mb.pm: $over_ascii, the multibyte anchor (5.038+/5.030+/
