    convention.  A blanket inheritance of UTF8::R2's ur2_* qr suite was
    EVALUATED and DECLINED: it is not additive.  ur2_* encodes mb8's
    octet-lenient \S/\H/\V semantics (a lone \x85 / \xA0 matches \S), whereas
    mb's documented codepoint \S matches only "a well-formed multi-byte
    sequence OR a US-ASCII byte [\x00-\x7F]", so a lone stray octet matches
    neither and a direct port produces 6 not-ok per qr file (e.g. assertions
    317/318/327/328/337/338 in ur2_1020_qr1).  This is mb-0.63's long-standing
    behaviour, not a port regression, so per the zero-regression rule the bulk
    inheritance is withdrawn; selective inheritance of non-diverging ur2_* cases
    remains possible as a future per-file-vetted additive sub-step.
