  - feature lib/mb.pm (step 5): port two runtime functions from mb8-0.01.
    sub mb::valid(;$) (about 13 lines) is inserted right before
    sub mb::require(); it is a non-destructive predicate that whole-matches
    its argument (or $_) against the STRICT unit ($over_ascii or a US-ASCII
    byte, NOT the lenient $x), returning 1 for well-formed input and 0 when
