  - audit lib/mb.pm (step 4): perl 5.005_03 read-only-value audit of every
    destructive s/// and tr/// in the code region.  Result: no new code change
    is required.  No destructive s///|tr/// is applied to $_[n], to a string
    literal, or to a bare read-only $_; every such target is a fresh writable
    lexical (copy-first idioms (my $c = $src) =~ s///, my($c) = @_, and
    my $c = $_[n]).  The one runtime sub that may receive a qr// argument and
    substitutes on it, _r2_qr(), already copies first via my $source = "$_[0]"
